<div id="review_831492631" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/831492631" />
    <a title="Jenny (Reading Envy)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68030-jenny-reading-envy"><img alt="Jenny (Reading Envy)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1455391853p2/68030.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/831492631?book_show_action=true">Jan 22, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jenny (Reading Envy)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jenny (Reading Envy)" href="/user/show/68030-jenny-reading-envy">Jenny (Reading Envy)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audio 9780804193986" href="/book/show/18594701-i-shall-be-near-to-you">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68030-jenny-reading-envy?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68030-jenny-reading-envy?shelf=read2014">read2014</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68030-jenny-reading-envy?shelf=reviewcopy">reviewcopy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer831492631" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7010756435428174438">Based on letters written during the War Between the States (Civil War, War of Northern Aggression, I&apos;m trying to take the middle ground here), I Shall Be Near to You tries to encapsulate the topic of women soldiers during the war, who had to pass as men to enlist.<br/><br/>In this story, all the historical research and discovered letters are consolidated into the narrative of one couple - Jeremiah and Rosetta. It is part love story, part war story, and is a pretty mild story of a very brief period of the </span>
  <span id="freeText7010756435428174438" style="display:none">Based on letters written during the War Between the States (Civil War, War of Northern Aggression, I'm trying to take the middle ground here), I Shall Be Near to You tries to encapsulate the topic of women soldiers during the war, who had to pass as men to enlist.<br /><br />In this story, all the historical research and discovered letters are consolidated into the narrative of one couple - Jeremiah and Rosetta. It is part love story, part war story, and is a pretty mild story of a very brief period of the war. I think I would have preferred if the author had written it as letters, but that wouldn't have worked as most of the time the characters are all in the same place. Something about the clumping together of so many different people oversimplifies the narrative and it wasn't as interesting as other war-time books I have read. I have a book of letters from the southern side of the war to read this year, and I imagine they will be more gritty, with a more realistic account of the agony and pain of war. <br /><br /><i>I received a copy of the audiobook in exchange for an honest review.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="7010756435428174438" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


